325 /// This allocates space for the specified virtual register to be held on the ----
326 /// stack. ----
327 int RegAllocFast::getStackSpaceFor(Register VirtReg) { 0
328 // Find the location Reg would belong... ----
329 int SS = StackSlotForVirtReg[VirtReg]; 0
330 // Already has space allocated? ----
331 if (SS != -1) 0
332 return SS; 0
333 ----
334 // Allocate a new stack object for this spill location... ----
335 const TargetRegisterClass &RC = *MRI->getRegClass(VirtReg); 0
336 unsigned Size = TRI->getSpillSize(RC); 0
337 Align Alignment = TRI->getSpillAlign(RC); 0
338 int FrameIdx = MFI->CreateSpillStackObject(Size, Alignment); 0
339 ----
340 // Assign the slot. ----
341 StackSlotForVirtReg[VirtReg] = FrameIdx; 0
342 return FrameIdx; 0
343 } ----

345 static bool dominates(MachineBasicBlock &MBB, 0
346 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator A, ----
347 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator B) { ----
348 auto MBBEnd = MBB.end(); 0
349 if (B == MBBEnd) 0
350 return true; 0
351 ----
352 MachineBasicBlock::const_iterator I = MBB.begin(); 0
353 for (; &*I != A && &*I != B; ++I) 0
354 ; ----
355 ----
356 return &*I == A; 0
357 } ----

359 /// Returns false if \p VirtReg is known to not live out of the current block. ----
360 bool RegAllocFast::mayLiveOut(Register VirtReg) { 0
361 if (MayLiveAcrossBlocks.test(Register::virtReg2Index(VirtReg))) { 0
362 // Cannot be live-out if there are no successors. ----
363 return !MBB->succ_empty(); 0
364 } ----
365 ----
366 const MachineInstr *SelfLoopDef = nullptr; 0
367 ----
368 // If this block loops back to itself, it is necessary to check whether the ----
369 // use comes after the def. ----
370 if (MBB->isSuccessor(MBB)) { 0
371 // Find the first def in the self loop MBB. ----
372 for (const MachineInstr &DefInst : MRI->def_instructions(VirtReg)) { 0
373 if (DefInst.getParent() != MBB) { 0
374 MayLiveAcrossBlocks.set(Register::virtReg2Index(VirtReg)); 0
375 return true; 0
376 } else { ----
377 if (!SelfLoopDef || dominates(*MBB, DefInst.getIterator(), SelfLoopDef)) 0
378 SelfLoopDef = &DefInst; 0
379 } ----
380 } ----
381 if (!SelfLoopDef) { 0
382 MayLiveAcrossBlocks.set(Register::virtReg2Index(VirtReg)); 0
383 return true; 0
384 } ----
385 } ----
386 ----
387 // See if the first \p Limit uses of the register are all in the current ----
388 // block. ----
389 static const unsigned Limit = 8; ----
390 unsigned C = 0; 0
391 for (const MachineInstr &UseInst : MRI->use_nodbg_instructions(VirtReg)) { 0
392 if (UseInst.getParent() != MBB || ++C >= Limit) { 0
393 MayLiveAcrossBlocks.set(Register::virtReg2Index(VirtReg)); 0
394 // Cannot be live-out if there are no successors. ----
395 return !MBB->succ_empty(); 0
396 } ----
397 ----
398 if (SelfLoopDef) { 0
399 // Try to handle some simple cases to avoid spilling and reloading every ----
400 // value inside a self looping block. ----
401 if (SelfLoopDef == &UseInst || 0
402 !dominates(*MBB, SelfLoopDef->getIterator(), UseInst.getIterator())) { 0
403 MayLiveAcrossBlocks.set(Register::virtReg2Index(VirtReg)); 0
404 return true; 0
405 } ----
406 } ----
407 } ----
408 ----
409 return false; 0
410 } ----
411 ----
412 /// Returns false if \p VirtReg is known to not be live into the current block. ----
413 bool RegAllocFast::mayLiveIn(Register VirtReg) { 0
414 if (MayLiveAcrossBlocks.test(Register::virtReg2Index(VirtReg))) 0
415 return !MBB->pred_empty(); 0
416 ----
417 // See if the first \p Limit def of the register are all in the current block. ----
418 static const unsigned Limit = 8; ----
419 unsigned C = 0; 0
420 for (const MachineInstr &DefInst : MRI->def_instructions(VirtReg)) { 0
421 if (DefInst.getParent() != MBB || ++C >= Limit) { 0
422 MayLiveAcrossBlocks.set(Register::virtReg2Index(VirtReg)); 0
423 return !MBB->pred_empty(); 0
424 } ----
425 } ----
426 ----
427 return false; 0
428 } ----

430 /// Insert spill instruction for \p AssignedReg before \p Before. Update ----
431 /// DBG_VALUEs with \p VirtReg operands with the stack slot. ----
432 void RegAllocFast::spill(MachineBasicBlock::iterator Before, Register VirtReg, 0
433 MCPhysReg AssignedReg, bool Kill, bool LiveOut) { ----
434 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Spilling " << printReg(VirtReg, TRI) 0
435 << " in " << printReg(AssignedReg, TRI)); ----
436 int FI = getStackSpaceFor(VirtReg); 0
437 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << " to stack slot #" << FI << '\n'); 0
438 ----
439 const TargetRegisterClass &RC = *MRI->getRegClass(VirtReg); 0
440 TII->storeRegToStackSlot(*MBB, Before, AssignedReg, Kill, FI, &RC, TRI, 0
441 VirtReg); ----
442 ++NumStores; 0
443 ----
444 MachineBasicBlock::iterator FirstTerm = MBB->getFirstTerminator(); 0
445 ----
446 // When we spill a virtual register, we will have spill instructions behind ----
447 // every definition of it, meaning we can switch all the DBG_VALUEs over ----
448 // to just reference the stack slot. ----
449 SmallVectorImpl &LRIDbgOperands = LiveDbgValueMap[VirtReg]; 0
450 SmallMapVector, 2> ----
451 SpilledOperandsMap; 0
452 for (MachineOperand *MO : LRIDbgOperands) 0
453 SpilledOperandsMap[MO->getParent()].push_back(MO); 0
454 for (auto MISpilledOperands : SpilledOperandsMap) { 0
455 MachineInstr &DBG = *MISpilledOperands.first; 0
456 // We don't have enough support for tracking operands of DBG_VALUE_LISTs. ----
457 if (DBG.isDebugValueList()) 0
458 continue; 0
459 MachineInstr *NewDV = buildDbgValueForSpill( 0
460 *MBB, Before, *MISpilledOperands.first, FI, MISpilledOperands.second); 0
461 assert(NewDV->getParent() == MBB && "dangling parent pointer"); 0
462 (void)NewDV; ----
463 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Inserting debug info due to spill:\n" << *NewDV); 0
464 ----
465 if (LiveOut) { 0
466 // We need to insert a DBG_VALUE at the end of the block if the spill slot ----
467 // is live out, but there is another use of the value after the ----
468 // spill. This will allow LiveDebugValues to see the correct live out ----
469 // value to propagate to the successors. ----
470 MachineInstr *ClonedDV = MBB->getParent()->CloneMachineInstr(NewDV); 0
471 MBB->insert(FirstTerm, ClonedDV); 0
472 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Cloning debug info due to live out spill\n"); 0
473 } ----
474 ----
475 // Rewrite unassigned dbg_values to use the stack slot. ----
476 // TODO We can potentially do this for list debug values as well if we know ----
477 // how the dbg_values are getting unassigned. ----
478 if (DBG.isNonListDebugValue()) { 0
479 MachineOperand &MO = DBG.getDebugOperand(0); 0
480 if (MO.isReg() && MO.getReg() == 0) { 0
481 updateDbgValueForSpill(DBG, FI, 0); 0
482 } ----
483 } ----
484 } 0
485 // Now this register is spilled there is should not be any DBG_VALUE ----
486 // pointing to this register because they are all pointing to spilled value ----
487 // now. ----
488 LRIDbgOperands.clear(); 0
489 } 0

491 /// Insert reload instruction for \p PhysReg before \p Before. ----
492 void RegAllocFast::reload(MachineBasicBlock::iterator Before, Register VirtReg, 0
493 MCPhysReg PhysReg) { ----
494 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Reloading " << printReg(VirtReg, TRI) << " into " 0
495 << printReg(PhysReg, TRI) << '\n'); ----
496 int FI = getStackSpaceFor(VirtReg); 0
497 const TargetRegisterClass &RC = *MRI->getRegClass(VirtReg); 0
498 TII->loadRegFromStackSlot(*MBB, Before, PhysReg, FI, &RC, TRI, VirtReg); 0
499 ++NumLoads; 0
500 } 0
501 ----
502 /// Get basic block begin insertion point. ----
503 /// This is not just MBB.begin() because surprisingly we have EH_LABEL ----
504 /// instructions marking the begin of a basic block. This means we must insert ----
505 /// new instructions after such labels... ----
506 MachineBasicBlock::iterator ----
507 RegAllocFast::getMBBBeginInsertionPoint( 0
508 MachineBasicBlock &MBB, SmallSet &PrologLiveIns) const { ----
509 MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = MBB.begin(); 0
510 while (I != MBB.end()) { 0
511 if (I->isLabel()) { 0
512 ++I; 0
513 continue; 0
514 } ----
515 ----
516 // Most reloads should be inserted after prolog instructions. ----
517 if (!TII->isBasicBlockPrologue(*I)) 0
518 break; 0
519 ----
520 // However if a prolog instruction reads a register that needs to be ----
521 // reloaded, the reload should be inserted before the prolog. ----
522 for (MachineOperand &MO : I->operands()) { 0
523 if (MO.isReg()) 0
524 PrologLiveIns.insert(MO.getReg()); 0
525 } ----
526 ----
527 ++I; 0
528 } ----
529 ----
530 return I; 0
531 } ----
532 ----
533 /// Reload all currently assigned virtual registers. ----
534 void RegAllocFast::reloadAtBegin(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
535 if (LiveVirtRegs.empty()) 0
536 return; 0
537 ----
538 for (MachineBasicBlock::RegisterMaskPair P : MBB.liveins()) { 0
539 MCPhysReg Reg = P.PhysReg; 0
540 // Set state to live-in. This possibly overrides mappings to virtual ----
541 // registers but we don't care anymore at this point. ----
542 setPhysRegState(Reg, regLiveIn); 0
543 } ----
544 ----
545 ----
546 SmallSet PrologLiveIns; 0
547 ----
548 // The LiveRegMap is keyed by an unsigned (the virtreg number), so the order ----
549 // of spilling here is deterministic, if arbitrary. ----
550 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore ----
551 = getMBBBeginInsertionPoint(MBB, PrologLiveIns); 0
552 for (const LiveReg &LR : LiveVirtRegs) { 0
553 MCPhysReg PhysReg = LR.PhysReg; 0
554 if (PhysReg == 0) 0
555 continue; 0
556 ----
557 MCRegister FirstUnit = *TRI->regunits(PhysReg).begin(); 0
558 if (RegUnitStates[FirstUnit] == regLiveIn) 0
559 continue; 0
560 ----
561 assert((&MBB != &MBB.getParent()->front() || IgnoreMissingDefs) && 0
562 "no reload in start block. Missing vreg def?"); ----
563 ----
564 if (PrologLiveIns.count(PhysReg)) { 0
565 // FIXME: Theoretically this should use an insert point skipping labels ----
566 // but I'm not sure how labels should interact with prolog instruction ----
567 // that need reloads. ----
568 reload(MBB.begin(), LR.VirtReg, PhysReg); 0
569 } else ----
570 reload(InsertBefore, LR.VirtReg, PhysReg); 0
571 } ----
572 LiveVirtRegs.clear(); 0
573 } 0
574 ----
575 /// Handle the direct use of a physical register. Check that the register is ----
576 /// not used by a virtreg. Kill the physreg, marking it free. This may add ----
577 /// implicit kills to MO->getParent() and invalidate MO. ----
578 bool RegAllocFast::usePhysReg(MachineInstr &MI, MCPhysReg Reg) { 0
579 assert(Register::isPhysicalRegister(Reg) && "expected physreg"); 0
580 bool displacedAny = displacePhysReg(MI, Reg); 0
581 setPhysRegState(Reg, regPreAssigned); 0
582 markRegUsedInInstr(Reg); 0
583 return displacedAny; 0
584 } ----
585 ----
586 bool RegAllocFast::definePhysReg(MachineInstr &MI, MCPhysReg Reg) { 0
587 bool displacedAny = displacePhysReg(MI, Reg); 0
588 setPhysRegState(Reg, regPreAssigned); 0
589 return displacedAny; 0
590 } ----
591 ----
592 /// Mark PhysReg as reserved or free after spilling any virtregs. This is very ----
593 /// similar to defineVirtReg except the physreg is reserved instead of ----
594 /// allocated. ----
595 bool RegAllocFast::displacePhysReg(MachineInstr &MI, MCPhysReg PhysReg) { 0
596 bool displacedAny = false; 0
597 ----
598 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(PhysReg)) { 0
599 switch (unsigned VirtReg = RegUnitStates[Unit]) { 0
600 default: { 0
601 LiveRegMap::iterator LRI = findLiveVirtReg(VirtReg); 0
602 assert(LRI != LiveVirtRegs.end() && "datastructures in sync"); 0
603 MachineBasicBlock::iterator ReloadBefore = ----
604 std::next((MachineBasicBlock::iterator)MI.getIterator()); 0
605 reload(ReloadBefore, VirtReg, LRI->PhysReg); 0
606 ----
607 setPhysRegState(LRI->PhysReg, regFree); 0
608 LRI->PhysReg = 0; 0
609 LRI->Reloaded = true; 0
610 displacedAny = true; 0
611 break; 0
612 } ----
613 case regPreAssigned: 0
614 RegUnitStates[Unit] = regFree; 0
615 displacedAny = true; 0
616 break; 0
617 case regFree: 0
618 break; 0
619 } ----
620 } ----
621 return displacedAny; 0
622 } ----

624 void RegAllocFast::freePhysReg(MCPhysReg PhysReg) { 0
625 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Freeing " << printReg(PhysReg, TRI) << ':'); 0
626 ----
627 MCRegister FirstUnit = *TRI->regunits(PhysReg).begin(); 0
628 switch (unsigned VirtReg = RegUnitStates[FirstUnit]) { 0
629 case regFree: 0
630 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << '\n'); 0
631 return; 0
632 case regPreAssigned: 0
633 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << '\n'); 0
634 setPhysRegState(PhysReg, regFree); 0
635 return; 0
636 default: { 0
637 LiveRegMap::iterator LRI = findLiveVirtReg(VirtReg); 0
638 assert(LRI != LiveVirtRegs.end()); 0
639 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << ' ' << printReg(LRI->VirtReg, TRI) << '\n'); 0
640 setPhysRegState(LRI->PhysReg, regFree); 0
641 LRI->PhysReg = 0; 0
642 } ----
643 return; 0
644 } ----
645 } ----
646 ----
647 /// Return the cost of spilling clearing out PhysReg and aliases so it is free ----
648 /// for allocation. Returns 0 when PhysReg is free or disabled with all aliases ----
649 /// disabled - it can be allocated directly. ----
650 /// \returns spillImpossible when PhysReg or an alias can't be spilled. ----
651 unsigned RegAllocFast::calcSpillCost(MCPhysReg PhysReg) const { 0
652 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(PhysReg)) { 0
653 switch (unsigned VirtReg = RegUnitStates[Unit]) { 0
654 case regFree: 0
655 break; 0
656 case regPreAssigned: 0
657 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Cannot spill pre-assigned " 0
658 << printReg(PhysReg, TRI) << '\n'); ----
659 return spillImpossible; 0
660 default: { 0
661 bool SureSpill = StackSlotForVirtReg[VirtReg] != -1 || 0
662 findLiveVirtReg(VirtReg)->LiveOut; 0
663 return SureSpill ? spillClean : spillDirty; 0
664 } ----
665 } ----
666 } ----
667 return 0; 0
668 } ----
669 ----
670 void RegAllocFast::assignDanglingDebugValues(MachineInstr &Definition, 0
671 Register VirtReg, MCPhysReg Reg) { ----
672 auto UDBGValIter = DanglingDbgValues.find(VirtReg); 0
673 if (UDBGValIter == DanglingDbgValues.end()) 0
674 return; 0
675 ----
676 SmallVectorImpl &Dangling = UDBGValIter->second; 0
677 for (MachineInstr *DbgValue : Dangling) { 0
678 assert(DbgValue->isDebugValue()); 0
679 if (!DbgValue->hasDebugOperandForReg(VirtReg)) 0
680 continue; 0
681 ----
682 // Test whether the physreg survives from the definition to the DBG_VALUE. ----
683 MCPhysReg SetToReg = Reg; 0
684 unsigned Limit = 20; 0
685 for (MachineBasicBlock::iterator I = std::next(Definition.getIterator()), 0
686 E = DbgValue->getIterator(); I != E; ++I) { 0
687 if (I->modifiesRegister(Reg, TRI) || --Limit == 0) { 0
688 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Register did not survive for " << *DbgValue 0
689 << '\n'); ----
690 SetToReg = 0; 0
691 break; 0
692 } ----
693 } ----
694 for (MachineOperand &MO : DbgValue->getDebugOperandsForReg(VirtReg)) { 0
695 MO.setReg(SetToReg); 0
696 if (SetToReg != 0) 0
697 MO.setIsRenamable(); 0
698 } 0
699 } ----
700 Dangling.clear(); 0
701 } ----
702 ----
703 /// This method updates local state so that we know that PhysReg is the ----
704 /// proper container for VirtReg now. The physical register must not be used ----
705 /// for anything else when this is called. ----
706 void RegAllocFast::assignVirtToPhysReg(MachineInstr &AtMI, LiveReg &LR, 0
707 MCPhysReg PhysReg) { ----
708 Register VirtReg = LR.VirtReg; 0
709 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Assigning " << printReg(VirtReg, TRI) << " to " 0
710 << printReg(PhysReg, TRI) << '\n'); ----
711 assert(LR.PhysReg == 0 && "Already assigned a physreg"); 0
712 assert(PhysReg != 0 && "Trying to assign no register"); 0
713 LR.PhysReg = PhysReg; 0
714 setPhysRegState(PhysReg, VirtReg); 0
715 ----
716 assignDanglingDebugValues(AtMI, VirtReg, PhysReg); 0
717 } 0
718 ----
719 static bool isCoalescable(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
720 return MI.isFullCopy(); 0
721 } ----
722 ----
723 Register RegAllocFast::traceCopyChain(Register Reg) const { 0
724 static const unsigned ChainLengthLimit = 3; ----
725 unsigned C = 0; 0
726 do { ----
727 if (Reg.isPhysical()) 0
728 return Reg; 0
729 assert(Reg.isVirtual()); 0
730 ----
731 MachineInstr *VRegDef = MRI->getUniqueVRegDef(Reg); 0
732 if (!VRegDef || !isCoalescable(*VRegDef)) 0
733 return 0; 0
734 Reg = VRegDef->getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
735 } while (++C <= ChainLengthLimit); 0
736 return 0; 0
737 } ----
738 ----
739 /// Check if any of \p VirtReg's definitions is a copy. If it is follow the ----
740 /// chain of copies to check whether we reach a physical register we can ----
741 /// coalesce with. ----
742 Register RegAllocFast::traceCopies(Register VirtReg) const { 0
743 static const unsigned DefLimit = 3; ----
744 unsigned C = 0; 0
745 for (const MachineInstr &MI : MRI->def_instructions(VirtReg)) { 0
746 if (isCoalescable(MI)) { 0
747 Register Reg = MI.getOperand(1).getReg(); 0
748 Reg = traceCopyChain(Reg); 0
749 if (Reg.isValid()) 0
750 return Reg; 0
751 } ----
752 ----
753 if (++C >= DefLimit) 0
754 break; 0
755 } ----
756 return Register(); 0
757 } ----
758 ----
759 /// Allocates a physical register for VirtReg. ----
760 void RegAllocFast::allocVirtReg(MachineInstr &MI, LiveReg &LR, 0
761 Register Hint0, bool LookAtPhysRegUses) { ----
762 const Register VirtReg = LR.VirtReg; 0
763 assert(LR.PhysReg == 0); 0
764 ----
765 const TargetRegisterClass &RC = *MRI->getRegClass(VirtReg); 0
766 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Search register for " << printReg(VirtReg) 0
767 << " in class " << TRI->getRegClassName(&RC) ----
768 << " with hint " << printReg(Hint0, TRI) << '\n'); ----
769 ----
770 // Take hint when possible. ----
771 if (Hint0.isPhysical() && MRI->isAllocatable(Hint0) && RC.contains(Hint0) && 0
772 !isRegUsedInInstr(Hint0, LookAtPhysRegUses)) { 0
773 // Take hint if the register is currently free. ----
774 if (isPhysRegFree(Hint0)) { 0
775 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tPreferred Register 1: " << printReg(Hint0, TRI) 0
776 << '\n'); ----
777 assignVirtToPhysReg(MI, LR, Hint0); 0
778 return; 0
779 } else { ----
780 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tPreferred Register 0: " << printReg(Hint0, TRI) 0
781 << " occupied\n"); ----
782 } ----
783 } else { ----
784 Hint0 = Register(); 0
785 } ----
786 ----
787 ----
788 // Try other hint. ----
789 Register Hint1 = traceCopies(VirtReg); 0
790 if (Hint1.isPhysical() && MRI->isAllocatable(Hint1) && RC.contains(Hint1) && 0
791 !isRegUsedInInstr(Hint1, LookAtPhysRegUses)) { 0
792 // Take hint if the register is currently free. ----
793 if (isPhysRegFree(Hint1)) { 0
794 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tPreferred Register 0: " << printReg(Hint1, TRI) 0
795 << '\n'); ----
796 assignVirtToPhysReg(MI, LR, Hint1); 0
797 return; 0
798 } else { ----
799 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tPreferred Register 1: " << printReg(Hint1, TRI) 0
800 << " occupied\n"); ----
801 } ----
802 } else { ----
803 Hint1 = Register(); 0
804 } ----
805 ----
806 MCPhysReg BestReg = 0; 0
807 unsigned BestCost = spillImpossible; 0
808 ArrayRef AllocationOrder = RegClassInfo.getOrder(&RC); 0
809 for (MCPhysReg PhysReg : AllocationOrder) { 0
810 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\tRegister: " << printReg(PhysReg, TRI) << ' '); 0
811 if (isRegUsedInInstr(PhysReg, LookAtPhysRegUses)) { 0
812 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "already used in instr.\n"); 0
813 continue; 0
814 } ----
815 ----
816 unsigned Cost = calcSpillCost(PhysReg); 0
817 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Cost: " << Cost << " BestCost: " << BestCost << '\n'); 0
818 // Immediate take a register with cost 0. ----
819 if (Cost == 0) { 0
820 assignVirtToPhysReg(MI, LR, PhysReg); 0
821 return; 0
822 } ----
823 ----
824 if (PhysReg == Hint0 || PhysReg == Hint1) 0
825 Cost -= spillPrefBonus; 0
826 ----
827 if (Cost < BestCost) { 0
828 BestReg = PhysReg; 0
829 BestCost = Cost; 0
830 } ----
831 } ----
832 ----
833 if (!BestReg) { 0
834 // Nothing we can do: Report an error and keep going with an invalid ----
835 // allocation. ----
836 if (MI.isInlineAsm()) 0
837 MI.emitError("inline assembly requires more registers than available"); 0
838 else ----
839 MI.emitError("ran out of registers during register allocation"); 0
840 ----
841 LR.Error = true; 0
842 LR.PhysReg = 0; 0
843 return; 0
844 } ----
845 ----
846 displacePhysReg(MI, BestReg); 0
847 assignVirtToPhysReg(MI, LR, BestReg); 0
848 } ----
849 ----
850 void RegAllocFast::allocVirtRegUndef(MachineOperand &MO) { 0
851 assert(MO.isUndef() && "expected undef use"); 0
852 Register VirtReg = MO.getReg(); 0
853 assert(VirtReg.isVirtual() && "Expected virtreg"); 0
854 if (!shouldAllocateRegister(VirtReg)) 0
855 return; 0
856 ----
857 LiveRegMap::const_iterator LRI = findLiveVirtReg(VirtReg); 0
858 MCPhysReg PhysReg; ----
859 if (LRI != LiveVirtRegs.end() && LRI->PhysReg) { 0
860 PhysReg = LRI->PhysReg; 0
861 } else { ----
862 const TargetRegisterClass &RC = *MRI->getRegClass(VirtReg); 0
863 ArrayRef AllocationOrder = RegClassInfo.getOrder(&RC); 0
864 assert(!AllocationOrder.empty() && "Allocation order must not be empty"); 0
865 PhysReg = AllocationOrder[0]; 0
866 } ----
867 ----
868 unsigned SubRegIdx = MO.getSubReg(); 0
869 if (SubRegIdx != 0) { 0
870 PhysReg = TRI->getSubReg(PhysReg, SubRegIdx); 0
871 MO.setSubReg(0); 0
872 } ----
873 MO.setReg(PhysReg); 0
874 MO.setIsRenamable(true); 0
875 } ----
876 ----
877 /// Variation of defineVirtReg() with special handling for livethrough regs ----
878 /// (tied or earlyclobber) that may interfere with preassigned uses. ----
879 /// \return true if MI's MachineOperands were re-arranged/invalidated. ----
880 bool RegAllocFast::defineLiveThroughVirtReg(MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpNum, 0
881 Register VirtReg) { ----
882 if (!shouldAllocateRegister(VirtReg)) 0
883 return false; 0
884 LiveRegMap::iterator LRI = findLiveVirtReg(VirtReg); 0
885 if (LRI != LiveVirtRegs.end()) { 0
886 MCPhysReg PrevReg = LRI->PhysReg; 0
887 if (PrevReg != 0 && isRegUsedInInstr(PrevReg, true)) { 0
888 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Need new assignment for " << printReg(PrevReg, TRI) 0
889 << " (tied/earlyclobber resolution)\n"); ----
890 freePhysReg(PrevReg); 0
891 LRI->PhysReg = 0; 0
892 allocVirtReg(MI, *LRI, 0, true); 0
893 MachineBasicBlock::iterator InsertBefore = ----
894 std::next((MachineBasicBlock::iterator)MI.getIterator()); 0
895 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Copy " << printReg(LRI->PhysReg, TRI) << " to " 0
896 << printReg(PrevReg, TRI) << '\n'); ----
897 BuildMI(*MBB, InsertBefore, MI.getDebugLoc(), 0
898 TII->get(TargetOpcode::COPY), PrevReg) 0
899 .addReg(LRI->PhysReg, llvm::RegState::Kill); 0
900 } ----
901 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(OpNum); 0
902 if (MO.getSubReg() && !MO.isUndef()) { 0
903 LRI->LastUse = &MI; 0
904 } ----
905 } ----
906 return defineVirtReg(MI, OpNum, VirtReg, true); 0
907 } ----
908 ----
909 /// Allocates a register for VirtReg definition. Typically the register is ----
910 /// already assigned from a use of the virtreg, however we still need to ----
911 /// perform an allocation if: ----
912 /// - It is a dead definition without any uses. ----
913 /// - The value is live out and all uses are in different basic blocks. ----
914 /// ----
915 /// \return true if MI's MachineOperands were re-arranged/invalidated. ----
916 bool RegAllocFast::defineVirtReg(MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpNum, 0
917 Register VirtReg, bool LookAtPhysRegUses) { ----
918 assert(VirtReg.isVirtual() && "Not a virtual register"); 0
919 if (!shouldAllocateRegister(VirtReg)) 0
920 return false; 0
921 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(OpNum); 0
922 LiveRegMap::iterator LRI; ----
923 bool New; ----
924 std::tie(LRI, New) = LiveVirtRegs.insert(LiveReg(VirtReg)); 0
925 if (New) { 0
926 if (!MO.isDead()) { 0
927 if (mayLiveOut(VirtReg)) { 0
928 LRI->LiveOut = true; 0
929 } else { ----
930 // It is a dead def without the dead flag; add the flag now. ----
931 MO.setIsDead(true); 0
932 } ----
933 } ----
934 } ----
935 if (LRI->PhysReg == 0) { 0
936 allocVirtReg(MI, *LRI, 0, LookAtPhysRegUses); 0
937 // If no physical register is available for LRI, we assign one at random ----
938 // and bail out of this function immediately. ----
939 if (LRI->Error) { 0
940 const TargetRegisterClass &RC = *MRI->getRegClass(VirtReg); 0
941 ArrayRef AllocationOrder = RegClassInfo.getOrder(&RC); 0
942 if (AllocationOrder.empty()) 0
943 return setPhysReg(MI, MO, MCRegister::NoRegister); 0
944 return setPhysReg(MI, MO, *AllocationOrder.begin()); 0
945 } ----
946 } else { ----
947 assert(!isRegUsedInInstr(LRI->PhysReg, LookAtPhysRegUses) && 0
948 "TODO: preassign mismatch"); ----
949 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "In def of " << printReg(VirtReg, TRI) 0
950 << " use existing assignment to " ----
951 << printReg(LRI->PhysReg, TRI) << '\n'); ----
952 } ----
953 ----
954 MCPhysReg PhysReg = LRI->PhysReg; 0
955 if (LRI->Reloaded || LRI->LiveOut) { 0
956 if (!MI.isImplicitDef()) { 0
957 MachineBasicBlock::iterator SpillBefore = ----
958 std::next((MachineBasicBlock::iterator)MI.getIterator()); 0
959 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Spill Reason: LO: " << LRI->LiveOut << " RL: " 0
960 << LRI->Reloaded << '\n'); ----
961 bool Kill = LRI->LastUse == nullptr; 0
962 spill(SpillBefore, VirtReg, PhysReg, Kill, LRI->LiveOut); 0
963 ----
964 // We need to place additional spills for each indirect destination of an ----
965 // INLINEASM_BR. ----
966 if (MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::INLINEASM_BR) { 0
967 int FI = StackSlotForVirtReg[VirtReg]; 0
968 const TargetRegisterClass &RC = *MRI->getRegClass(VirtReg); 0
969 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
970 if (MO.isMBB()) { 0
971 MachineBasicBlock *Succ = MO.getMBB(); 0
972 TII->storeRegToStackSlot(*Succ, Succ->begin(), PhysReg, Kill, 0
973 FI, &RC, TRI, VirtReg); ----
974 ++NumStores; 0
975 Succ->addLiveIn(PhysReg); 0
976 } ----
977 } ----
978 } ----
979 ----
980 LRI->LastUse = nullptr; 0
981 } ----
982 LRI->LiveOut = false; 0
983 LRI->Reloaded = false; 0
984 } ----
985 if (MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::BUNDLE) { 0
986 BundleVirtRegsMap[VirtReg] = PhysReg; 0
987 } ----
988 markRegUsedInInstr(PhysReg); 0
989 return setPhysReg(MI, MO, PhysReg); 0
990 } ----
991 ----
992 /// Allocates a register for a VirtReg use. ----
993 /// \return true if MI's MachineOperands were re-arranged/invalidated. ----
994 bool RegAllocFast::useVirtReg(MachineInstr &MI, unsigned OpNum, 0
995 Register VirtReg) { ----
996 assert(VirtReg.isVirtual() && "Not a virtual register"); 0
997 if (!shouldAllocateRegister(VirtReg)) 0
998 return false; 0
999 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(OpNum); 0
1000 LiveRegMap::iterator LRI; ----
1001 bool New; ----
1002 std::tie(LRI, New) = LiveVirtRegs.insert(LiveReg(VirtReg)); 0
1003 if (New) { 0
1004 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(OpNum); 0
1005 if (!MO.isKill()) { 0
1006 if (mayLiveOut(VirtReg)) { 0
1007 LRI->LiveOut = true; 0
1008 } else { ----
1009 // It is a last (killing) use without the kill flag; add the flag now. ----
1010 MO.setIsKill(true); 0
1011 } ----
1012 } ----
1013 } else { ----
1014 assert((!MO.isKill() || LRI->LastUse == &MI) && "Invalid kill flag"); 0
1015 } ----
1016 ----
1017 // If necessary allocate a register. ----
1018 if (LRI->PhysReg == 0) { 0
1019 assert(!MO.isTied() && "tied op should be allocated"); 0
1020 Register Hint; 0
1021 if (MI.isCopy() && MI.getOperand(1).getSubReg() == 0) { 0
1022 Hint = MI.getOperand(0).getReg(); 0
1023 if (Hint.isVirtual()) { 0
1024 assert(!shouldAllocateRegister(Hint)); 0
1025 Hint = Register(); 0
1026 } else { ----
1027 assert(Hint.isPhysical() && 0
1028 "Copy destination should already be assigned"); ----
1029 } ----
1030 } ----
1031 allocVirtReg(MI, *LRI, Hint, false); 0
1032 if (LRI->Error) { 0
1033 const TargetRegisterClass &RC = *MRI->getRegClass(VirtReg); 0
1034 ArrayRef AllocationOrder = RegClassInfo.getOrder(&RC); 0
1035 if (AllocationOrder.empty()) 0
1036 return setPhysReg(MI, MO, MCRegister::NoRegister); 0
1037 return setPhysReg(MI, MO, *AllocationOrder.begin()); 0
1038 } ----
1039 } ----
1040 ----
1041 LRI->LastUse = &MI; 0
1042 ----
1043 if (MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::BUNDLE) { 0
1044 BundleVirtRegsMap[VirtReg] = LRI->PhysReg; 0
1045 } ----
1046 markRegUsedInInstr(LRI->PhysReg); 0
1047 return setPhysReg(MI, MO, LRI->PhysReg); 0
1048 } ----
1049 ----
1050 /// Changes operand OpNum in MI the refer the PhysReg, considering subregs. ----
1051 /// \return true if MI's MachineOperands were re-arranged/invalidated. ----
1052 bool RegAllocFast::setPhysReg(MachineInstr &MI, MachineOperand &MO, 0
1053 MCPhysReg PhysReg) { ----
1054 if (!MO.getSubReg()) { 0
1055 MO.setReg(PhysReg); 0
1056 MO.setIsRenamable(true); 0
1057 return false; 0
1058 } ----
1059 ----
1060 // Handle subregister index. ----
1061 MO.setReg(PhysReg ? TRI->getSubReg(PhysReg, MO.getSubReg()) : MCRegister()); 0
1062 MO.setIsRenamable(true); 0
1063 // Note: We leave the subreg number around a little longer in case of defs. ----
1064 // This is so that the register freeing logic in allocateInstruction can still ----
1065 // recognize this as subregister defs. The code there will clear the number. ----
1066 if (!MO.isDef()) 0
1067 MO.setSubReg(0); 0
1068 ----
1069 // A kill flag implies killing the full register. Add corresponding super ----
1070 // register kill. ----
1071 if (MO.isKill()) { 0
1072 MI.addRegisterKilled(PhysReg, TRI, true); 0
1073 // Conservatively assume implicit MOs were re-arranged ----
1074 return true; 0
1075 } ----
1076 ----
1077 // A of a sub-register requires an implicit def of the full ----
1078 // register. ----
1079 if (MO.isDef() && MO.isUndef()) { 0
1080 if (MO.isDead()) 0
1081 MI.addRegisterDead(PhysReg, TRI, true); 0
1082 else ----
1083 MI.addRegisterDefined(PhysReg, TRI); 0
1084 // Conservatively assume implicit MOs were re-arranged ----
1085 return true; 0
1086 } ----
1087 return false; 0
1088 } ----
1089 ----
1090 #ifndef NDEBUG ----
1091 ----
1092 void RegAllocFast::dumpState() const { 0
1093 for (unsigned Unit = 1, UnitE = TRI->getNumRegUnits(); Unit != UnitE; 0
1094 ++Unit) { ----
1095 switch (unsigned VirtReg = RegUnitStates[Unit]) { 0
1096 case regFree: 0
1097 break; 0
1098 case regPreAssigned: 0
1099 dbgs() << " " << printRegUnit(Unit, TRI) << "[P]"; 0
1100 break; 0
1101 case regLiveIn: 0
1102 llvm_unreachable("Should not have regLiveIn in map"); 0
1103 default: { 0
1104 dbgs() << ' ' << printRegUnit(Unit, TRI) << '=' << printReg(VirtReg); 0
1105 LiveRegMap::const_iterator I = findLiveVirtReg(VirtReg); 0
1106 assert(I != LiveVirtRegs.end() && "have LiveVirtRegs entry"); 0
1107 if (I->LiveOut || I->Reloaded) { 0
1108 dbgs() << '['; 0
1109 if (I->LiveOut) dbgs() << 'O'; 0
1110 if (I->Reloaded) dbgs() << 'R'; 0
1111 dbgs() << ']'; 0
1112 } ----
1113 assert(TRI->hasRegUnit(I->PhysReg, Unit) && "inverse mapping present"); 0
1114 break; 0
1115 } ----
1116 } ----
1117 } ----
1118 dbgs() << '\n'; 0
1119 // Check that LiveVirtRegs is the inverse. ----
1120 for (const LiveReg &LR : LiveVirtRegs) { 0
1121 Register VirtReg = LR.VirtReg; 0
1122 assert(VirtReg.isVirtual() && "Bad map key"); 0
1123 MCPhysReg PhysReg = LR.PhysReg; 0
1124 if (PhysReg != 0) { 0
1125 assert(Register::isPhysicalRegister(PhysReg) && 0
1126 "mapped to physreg"); ----
1127 for (MCRegUnit Unit : TRI->regunits(PhysReg)) { 0
1128 assert(RegUnitStates[Unit] == VirtReg && "inverse map valid"); 0
1129 } ----
1130 } ----
1131 } ----
1132 } 0
1133 #endif ----
1134 ----
1135 /// Count number of defs consumed from each register class by \p Reg ----
1136 void RegAllocFast::addRegClassDefCounts(std::vector &RegClassDefCounts, 0
1137 Register Reg) const { ----
1138 assert(RegClassDefCounts.size() == TRI->getNumRegClasses()); 0
1139 ----
1140 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
1141 if (!shouldAllocateRegister(Reg)) 0
1142 return; 0
1143 const TargetRegisterClass *OpRC = MRI->getRegClass(Reg); 0
1144 for (unsigned RCIdx = 0, RCIdxEnd = TRI->getNumRegClasses(); 0
1145 RCIdx != RCIdxEnd; ++RCIdx) { 0
1146 const TargetRegisterClass *IdxRC = TRI->getRegClass(RCIdx); 0
1147 // FIXME: Consider aliasing sub/super registers. ----
1148 if (OpRC->hasSubClassEq(IdxRC)) 0
1149 ++RegClassDefCounts[RCIdx]; 0
1150 } ----
1151 ----
1152 return; 0
1153 } ----
1154 ----
1155 for (unsigned RCIdx = 0, RCIdxEnd = TRI->getNumRegClasses(); 0
1156 RCIdx != RCIdxEnd; ++RCIdx) { 0
1157 const TargetRegisterClass *IdxRC = TRI->getRegClass(RCIdx); 0
1158 for (MCRegAliasIterator Alias(Reg, TRI, true); Alias.isValid(); ++Alias) { 0
1159 if (IdxRC->contains(*Alias)) { 0
1160 ++RegClassDefCounts[RCIdx]; 0
1161 break; 0
1162 } ----
1163 } ----
1164 } ----
1165 } ----
1166 ----
1167 /// Compute \ref DefOperandIndexes so it contains the indices of "def" operands ----
1168 /// that are to be allocated. Those are ordered in a way that small classes, ----
1169 /// early clobbers and livethroughs are allocated first. ----
1170 void RegAllocFast::findAndSortDefOperandIndexes(const MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1171 DefOperandIndexes.clear(); 0
1172 ----
1173 // Track number of defs which may consume a register from the class. ----
1174 std::vector RegClassDefCounts(TRI->getNumRegClasses(), 0); 0
1175 assert(RegClassDefCounts[0] == 0); 0
1176 ----
1177 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Need to assign livethroughs\n"); 0
1178 for (unsigned I = 0, E = MI.getNumOperands(); I < E; ++I) { 0
1179 const MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(I); 0
1180 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1181 continue; 0
1182 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1183 if (MO.readsReg()) { 0
1184 if (Reg.isPhysical()) { 0
1185 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "mark extra used: " << printReg(Reg, TRI) << '\n'); 0
1186 markPhysRegUsedInInstr(Reg); 0
1187 } ----
1188 } ----
1189 ----
1190 if (MO.isDef()) { 0
1191 if (Reg.isVirtual() && shouldAllocateRegister(Reg)) 0
1192 DefOperandIndexes.push_back(I); 0
1193 ----
1194 addRegClassDefCounts(RegClassDefCounts, Reg); 0
1195 } ----
1196 } ----
1197 ----
1198 llvm::sort(DefOperandIndexes, [&](uint16_t I0, uint16_t I1) { 0
1199 const MachineOperand &MO0 = MI.getOperand(I0); 0
1200 const MachineOperand &MO1 = MI.getOperand(I1); 0
1201 Register Reg0 = MO0.getReg(); 0
1202 Register Reg1 = MO1.getReg(); 0
1203 const TargetRegisterClass &RC0 = *MRI->getRegClass(Reg0); 0
1204 const TargetRegisterClass &RC1 = *MRI->getRegClass(Reg1); 0
1205 ----
1206 // Identify regclass that are easy to use up completely just in this ----
1207 // instruction. ----
1208 unsigned ClassSize0 = RegClassInfo.getOrder(&RC0).size(); 0
1209 unsigned ClassSize1 = RegClassInfo.getOrder(&RC1).size(); 0
1210 ----
1211 bool SmallClass0 = ClassSize0 < RegClassDefCounts[RC0.getID()]; 0
1212 bool SmallClass1 = ClassSize1 < RegClassDefCounts[RC1.getID()]; 0
1213 if (SmallClass0 > SmallClass1) 0
1214 return true; 0
1215 if (SmallClass0 < SmallClass1) 0
1216 return false; 0
1217 ----
1218 // Allocate early clobbers and livethrough operands first. ----
1219 bool Livethrough0 = MO0.isEarlyClobber() || MO0.isTied() || 0
1220 (MO0.getSubReg() == 0 && !MO0.isUndef()); 0
1221 bool Livethrough1 = MO1.isEarlyClobber() || MO1.isTied() || 0
1222 (MO1.getSubReg() == 0 && !MO1.isUndef()); 0
1223 if (Livethrough0 > Livethrough1) 0
1224 return true; 0
1225 if (Livethrough0 < Livethrough1) 0
1226 return false; 0
1227 ----
1228 // Tie-break rule: operand index. ----
1229 return I0 < I1; 0
1230 }); ----
1231 } 0
1232 ----
1233 void RegAllocFast::allocateInstruction(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1234 // The basic algorithm here is: ----
1235 // 1. Mark registers of def operands as free ----
1236 // 2. Allocate registers to use operands and place reload instructions for ----
1237 // registers displaced by the allocation. ----
1238 // ----
1239 // However we need to handle some corner cases: ----
1240 // - pre-assigned defs and uses need to be handled before the other def/use ----
1241 // operands are processed to avoid the allocation heuristics clashing with ----
1242 // the pre-assignment. ----
1243 // - The "free def operands" step has to come last instead of first for tied ----
1244 // operands and early-clobbers. ----
1245 ----
1246 UsedInInstr.clear(); 0
1247 RegMasks.clear(); 0
1248 BundleVirtRegsMap.clear(); 0
1249 ----
1250 auto TiedOpIsUndef = [&](const MachineOperand &MO, unsigned Idx) { 0
1251 assert(MO.isTied()); 0
1252 unsigned TiedIdx = MI.findTiedOperandIdx(Idx); 0
1253 const MachineOperand &TiedMO = MI.getOperand(TiedIdx); 0
1254 return TiedMO.isUndef(); 0
1255 }; 0
1256 // Scan for special cases; Apply pre-assigned register defs to state. ----
1257 bool HasPhysRegUse = false; 0
1258 bool HasRegMask = false; 0
1259 bool HasVRegDef = false; 0
1260 bool HasDef = false; 0
1261 bool HasEarlyClobber = false; 0
1262 bool NeedToAssignLiveThroughs = false; 0
1263 for (unsigned I = 0; I < MI.getNumOperands(); ++I) { 0
1264 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(I); 0
1265 if (MO.isReg()) { 0
1266 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1267 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
1268 if (!shouldAllocateRegister(Reg)) 0
1269 continue; 0
1270 if (MO.isDef()) { 0
1271 HasDef = true; 0
1272 HasVRegDef = true; 0
1273 if (MO.isEarlyClobber()) { 0
1274 HasEarlyClobber = true; 0
1275 NeedToAssignLiveThroughs = true; 0
1276 } ----
1277 if ((MO.isTied() && !TiedOpIsUndef(MO, I)) || 0
1278 (MO.getSubReg() != 0 && !MO.isUndef())) 0
1279 NeedToAssignLiveThroughs = true; 0
1280 } ----
1281 } else if (Reg.isPhysical()) { 0
1282 if (!MRI->isReserved(Reg)) { 0
1283 if (MO.isDef()) { 0
1284 HasDef = true; 0
1285 bool displacedAny = definePhysReg(MI, Reg); 0
1286 if (MO.isEarlyClobber()) 0
1287 HasEarlyClobber = true; 0
1288 if (!displacedAny) 0
1289 MO.setIsDead(true); 0
1290 } ----
1291 if (MO.readsReg()) 0
1292 HasPhysRegUse = true; 0
1293 } ----
1294 } ----
1295 } else if (MO.isRegMask()) { 0
1296 HasRegMask = true; 0
1297 RegMasks.push_back(MO.getRegMask()); 0
1298 } ----
1299 } ----
1300 ----
1301 // Allocate virtreg defs. ----
1302 if (HasDef) { 0
1303 if (HasVRegDef) { 0
1304 // Note that Implicit MOs can get re-arranged by defineVirtReg(), so loop ----
1305 // multiple times to ensure no operand is missed. ----
1306 bool ReArrangedImplicitOps = true; 0
1307 ----
1308 // Special handling for early clobbers, tied operands or subregister defs: ----
1309 // Compared to "normal" defs these: ----
1310 // - Must not use a register that is pre-assigned for a use operand. ----
1311 // - In order to solve tricky inline assembly constraints we change the ----
1312 // heuristic to figure out a good operand order before doing ----
1313 // assignments. ----
1314 if (NeedToAssignLiveThroughs) { 0
1315 PhysRegUses.clear(); 0
1316 ----
1317 while (ReArrangedImplicitOps) { 0
1318 ReArrangedImplicitOps = false; 0
1319 findAndSortDefOperandIndexes(MI); 0
1320 for (uint16_t OpIdx : DefOperandIndexes) { 0
1321 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(OpIdx); 0
1322 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Allocating " << MO << '\n'); 0
1323 unsigned Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1324 if (MO.isEarlyClobber() || 0
1325 (MO.isTied() && !TiedOpIsUndef(MO, OpIdx)) || 0
1326 (MO.getSubReg() && !MO.isUndef())) { 0
1327 ReArrangedImplicitOps = defineLiveThroughVirtReg(MI, OpIdx, Reg); 0
1328 } else { ----
1329 ReArrangedImplicitOps = defineVirtReg(MI, OpIdx, Reg); 0
1330 } ----
1331 if (ReArrangedImplicitOps) { 0
1332 // Implicit operands of MI were re-arranged, ----
1333 // re-compute DefOperandIndexes. ----
1334 break; 0
1335 } ----
1336 } ----
1337 } ----
1338 } else { ----
1339 // Assign virtual register defs. ----
1340 while (ReArrangedImplicitOps) { 0
1341 ReArrangedImplicitOps = false; 0
1342 for (unsigned I = 0, E = MI.getNumOperands(); I < E; ++I) { 0
1343 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(I); 0
1344 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isDef()) 0
1345 continue; 0
1346 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1347 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
1348 ReArrangedImplicitOps = defineVirtReg(MI, I, Reg); 0
1349 if (ReArrangedImplicitOps) { 0
1350 break; 0
1351 } ----
1352 } ----
1353 } ----
1354 } ----
1355 } ----
1356 } ----
1357 ----
1358 // Free registers occupied by defs. ----
1359 // Iterate operands in reverse order, so we see the implicit super register ----
1360 // defs first (we added them earlier in case of ). ----
1361 for (signed I = MI.getNumOperands() - 1; I >= 0; --I) { 0
1362 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(I); 0
1363 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isDef()) 0
1364 continue; 0
1365 ----
1366 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1367 ----
1368 // subreg defs don't free the full register. We left the subreg number ----
1369 // around as a marker in setPhysReg() to recognize this case here. ----
1370 if (Reg.isPhysical() && MO.getSubReg() != 0) { 0
1371 MO.setSubReg(0); 0
1372 continue; 0
1373 } ----
1374 ----
1375 assert((!MO.isTied() || !isClobberedByRegMasks(MO.getReg())) && 0
1376 "tied def assigned to clobbered register"); ----
1377 ----
1378 // Do not free tied operands and early clobbers. ----
1379 if ((MO.isTied() && !TiedOpIsUndef(MO, I)) || MO.isEarlyClobber()) 0
1380 continue; 0
1381 if (!Reg) 0
1382 continue; 0
1383 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
1384 assert(!shouldAllocateRegister(Reg)); 0
1385 continue; 0
1386 } ----
1387 assert(Reg.isPhysical()); 0
1388 if (MRI->isReserved(Reg)) 0
1389 continue; 0
1390 freePhysReg(Reg); 0
1391 unmarkRegUsedInInstr(Reg); 0
1392 } ----
1393 } ----
1394 ----
1395 // Displace clobbered registers. ----
1396 if (HasRegMask) { 0
1397 assert(!RegMasks.empty() && "expected RegMask"); 0
1398 // MRI bookkeeping. ----
1399 for (const auto *RM : RegMasks) 0
1400 MRI->addPhysRegsUsedFromRegMask(RM); 0
1401 ----
1402 // Displace clobbered registers. ----
1403 for (const LiveReg &LR : LiveVirtRegs) { 0
1404 MCPhysReg PhysReg = LR.PhysReg; 0
1405 if (PhysReg != 0 && isClobberedByRegMasks(PhysReg)) 0
1406 displacePhysReg(MI, PhysReg); 0
1407 } ----
1408 } ----
1409 ----
1410 // Apply pre-assigned register uses to state. ----
1411 if (HasPhysRegUse) { 0
1412 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.operands()) { 0
1413 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.readsReg()) 0
1414 continue; 0
1415 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1416 if (!Reg.isPhysical()) 0
1417 continue; 0
1418 if (MRI->isReserved(Reg)) 0
1419 continue; 0
1420 bool displacedAny = usePhysReg(MI, Reg); 0
1421 if (!displacedAny) 0
1422 MO.setIsKill(true); 0
1423 } ----
1424 } ----
1425 ----
1426 // Allocate virtreg uses and insert reloads as necessary. ----
1427 // Implicit MOs can get moved/removed by useVirtReg(), so loop multiple ----
1428 // times to ensure no operand is missed. ----
1429 bool HasUndefUse = false; 0
1430 bool ReArrangedImplicitMOs = true; 0
1431 while (ReArrangedImplicitMOs) { 0
1432 ReArrangedImplicitMOs = false; 0
1433 for (unsigned I = 0; I < MI.getNumOperands(); ++I) { 0
1434 MachineOperand &MO = MI.getOperand(I); 0
1435 if (!MO.isReg() || !MO.isUse()) 0
1436 continue; 0
1437 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1438 if (!Reg.isVirtual() || !shouldAllocateRegister(Reg)) 0
1439 continue; 0
1440 ----
1441 if (MO.isUndef()) { 0
1442 HasUndefUse = true; 0
1443 continue; 0
1444 } ----
1445 ----
1446 // Populate MayLiveAcrossBlocks in case the use block is allocated before ----
1447 // the def block (removing the vreg uses). ----
1448 mayLiveIn(Reg); 0
1449 ----
1450 assert(!MO.isInternalRead() && "Bundles not supported"); 0
1451 assert(MO.readsReg() && "reading use"); 0
1452 ReArrangedImplicitMOs = useVirtReg(MI, I, Reg); 0
1453 if (ReArrangedImplicitMOs) 0
1454 break; 0
1455 } ----
1456 } ----
1457 ----
1458 // Allocate undef operands. This is a separate step because in a situation ----
1459 // like ` = OP undef %X, %X` both operands need the same register assign ----
1460 // so we should perform the normal assignment first. ----
1461 if (HasUndefUse) { 0
1462 for (MachineOperand &MO : MI.all_uses()) { 0
1463 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1464 if (!Reg.isVirtual() || !shouldAllocateRegister(Reg)) 0
1465 continue; 0
1466 ----
1467 assert(MO.isUndef() && "Should only have undef virtreg uses left"); 0
1468 allocVirtRegUndef(MO); 0
1469 } ----
1470 } ----
1471 ----
1472 // Free early clobbers. ----
1473 if (HasEarlyClobber) { 0
1474 for (MachineOperand &MO : llvm::reverse(MI.all_defs())) { 0
1475 if (!MO.isEarlyClobber()) 0
1476 continue; 0
1477 assert(!MO.getSubReg() && "should be already handled in def processing"); 0
1478 ----
1479 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1480 if (!Reg) 0
1481 continue; 0
1482 if (Reg.isVirtual()) { 0
1483 assert(!shouldAllocateRegister(Reg)); 0
1484 continue; 0
1485 } ----
1486 assert(Reg.isPhysical() && "should have register assigned"); 0
1487 ----
1488 // We sometimes get odd situations like: ----
1489 // early-clobber %x0 = INSTRUCTION %x0 ----
1490 // which is semantically questionable as the early-clobber should ----
1491 // apply before the use. But in practice we consider the use to ----
1492 // happen before the early clobber now. Don't free the early clobber ----
1493 // register in this case. ----
1494 if (MI.readsRegister(Reg, TRI)) 0
1495 continue; 0
1496 ----
1497 freePhysReg(Reg); 0
1498 } ----
1499 } ----
1500 ----
1501 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "<< " << MI); 0
1502 if (MI.isCopy() && MI.getOperand(0).getReg() == MI.getOperand(1).getReg() && 0
1503 MI.getNumOperands() == 2) { 0
1504 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Mark identity copy for removal\n"); 0
1505 Coalesced.push_back(&MI); 0
1506 } ----
1507 } 0
1508 ----
1509 void RegAllocFast::handleDebugValue(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1510 // Ignore DBG_VALUEs that aren't based on virtual registers. These are ----
1511 // mostly constants and frame indices. ----
1512 for (Register Reg : MI.getUsedDebugRegs()) { 0
1513 if (!Reg.isVirtual()) 0
1514 continue; 0
1515 if (!shouldAllocateRegister(Reg)) 0
1516 continue; 0
1517 ----
1518 // Already spilled to a stackslot? ----
1519 int SS = StackSlotForVirtReg[Reg]; 0
1520 if (SS != -1) { 0
1521 // Modify DBG_VALUE now that the value is in a spill slot. ----
1522 updateDbgValueForSpill(MI, SS, Reg); 0
1523 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Rewrite DBG_VALUE for spilled memory: " << MI); 0
1524 continue; 0
1525 } ----
1526 ----
1527 // See if this virtual register has already been allocated to a physical ----
1528 // register or spilled to a stack slot. ----
1529 LiveRegMap::iterator LRI = findLiveVirtReg(Reg); 0
1530 SmallVector DbgOps; 0
1531 for (MachineOperand &Op : MI.getDebugOperandsForReg(Reg)) 0
1532 DbgOps.push_back(&Op); 0
1533 ----
1534 if (LRI != LiveVirtRegs.end() && LRI->PhysReg) { 0
1535 // Update every use of Reg within MI. ----
1536 for (auto &RegMO : DbgOps) 0
1537 setPhysReg(MI, *RegMO, LRI->PhysReg); 0
1538 } else { ----
1539 DanglingDbgValues[Reg].push_back(&MI); 0
1540 } ----
1541 ----
1542 // If Reg hasn't been spilled, put this DBG_VALUE in LiveDbgValueMap so ----
1543 // that future spills of Reg will have DBG_VALUEs. ----
1544 LiveDbgValueMap[Reg].append(DbgOps.begin(), DbgOps.end()); 0
1545 } 0
1546 } 0

1548 void RegAllocFast::handleBundle(MachineInstr &MI) { 0
1549 MachineBasicBlock::instr_iterator BundledMI = MI.getIterator(); 0
1550 ++BundledMI; 0
1551 while (BundledMI->isBundledWithPred()) { 0
1552 for (MachineOperand &MO : BundledMI->operands()) { 0
1553 if (!MO.isReg()) 0
1554 continue; 0
1555 ----
1556 Register Reg = MO.getReg(); 0
1557 if (!Reg.isVirtual() || !shouldAllocateRegister(Reg)) 0
1558 continue; 0
1559 ----
1560 DenseMap::iterator DI; 0
1561 DI = BundleVirtRegsMap.find(Reg); 0
1562 assert(DI != BundleVirtRegsMap.end() && "Unassigned virtual register"); 0
1563 ----
1564 setPhysReg(MI, MO, DI->second); 0
1565 } ----
1566 ----
1567 ++BundledMI; 0
1568 } ----
1569 } 0
1570 ----
1571 void RegAllocFast::allocateBasicBlock(MachineBasicBlock &MBB) { 0
1572 this->MBB = &MBB; 0
1573 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "\nAllocating " << MBB); 0
1574 ----
1575 RegUnitStates.assign(TRI->getNumRegUnits(), regFree); 0
1576 assert(LiveVirtRegs.empty() && "Mapping not cleared from last block?"); 0
1577 ----
1578 for (const auto &LiveReg : MBB.liveouts()) 0
1579 setPhysRegState(LiveReg.PhysReg, regPreAssigned); 0
1580 ----
1581 Coalesced.clear(); 0
1582 ----
1583 // Traverse block in reverse order allocating instructions one by one. ----
1584 for (MachineInstr &MI : reverse(MBB)) { 0
1585 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1586 dbgs() << "\n>> " << MI << "Regs:"; ----
1587 dumpState() ----
1588 ); ----
1589 ----
1590 // Special handling for debug values. Note that they are not allowed to ----
1591 // affect codegen of the other instructions in any way. ----
1592 if (MI.isDebugValue()) { 0
1593 handleDebugValue(MI); 0
1594 continue; 0
1595 } ----
1596 ----
1597 allocateInstruction(MI); 0
1598 ----
1599 // Once BUNDLE header is assigned registers, same assignments need to be ----
1600 // done for bundled MIs. ----
1601 if (MI.getOpcode() == TargetOpcode::BUNDLE) { 0
1602 handleBundle(MI); 0
1603 } ----
1604 } ----
1605 ----
1606 LLVM_DEBUG( 0
1607 dbgs() << "Begin Regs:"; ----
1608 dumpState() ----
1609 ); ----
1610 ----
1611 // Spill all physical registers holding virtual registers now. ----
1612 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Loading live registers at begin of block.\n"); 0
1613 reloadAtBegin(MBB); 0
1614 ----
1615 // Erase all the coalesced copies. We are delaying it until now because ----
1616 // LiveVirtRegs might refer to the instrs. ----
1617 for (MachineInstr *MI : Coalesced) 0
1618 MBB.erase(MI); 0
1619 NumCoalesced += Coalesced.size(); 0
1620 ----
1621 for (auto &UDBGPair : DanglingDbgValues) { 0
1622 for (MachineInstr *DbgValue : UDBGPair.second) { 0
1623 assert(DbgValue->isDebugValue() && "expected DBG_VALUE"); 0
1624 // Nothing to do if the vreg was spilled in the meantime. ----
1625 if (!DbgValue->hasDebugOperandForReg(UDBGPair.first)) 0
1626 continue; 0
1627 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "Register did not survive for " << *DbgValue 0
1628 << '\n'); ----
1629 DbgValue->setDebugValueUndef(); 0
1630 } ----
1631 } ----
1632 DanglingDbgValues.clear(); 0
1633 ----
1634 LLVM_DEBUG(MBB.dump()); 0
1635 } 0

1637 bool RegAllocFast::runOnMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) { 0
1638 LLVM_DEBUG(dbgs() << "********** FAST REGISTER ALLOCATION **********\n" 0
1639 << "********** Function: " << MF.getName() << '\n'); ----
1640 MRI = &MF.getRegInfo(); 0
1641 const TargetSubtargetInfo &STI = MF.getSubtarget(); 0
1642 TRI = STI.getRegisterInfo(); 0
1643 TII = STI.getInstrInfo(); 0
1644 MFI = &MF.getFrameInfo(); 0
1645 MRI->freezeReservedRegs(MF); 0
1646 RegClassInfo.runOnMachineFunction(MF); 0
1647 unsigned NumRegUnits = TRI->getNumRegUnits(); 0
1648 UsedInInstr.clear(); 0
1649 UsedInInstr.setUniverse(NumRegUnits); 0
1650 PhysRegUses.clear(); 0
1651 PhysRegUses.setUniverse(NumRegUnits); 0
1652 ----
1653 // initialize the virtual->physical register map to have a 'null' ----
1654 // mapping for all virtual registers ----
1655 unsigned NumVirtRegs = MRI->getNumVirtRegs(); 0
1656 StackSlotForVirtReg.resize(NumVirtRegs); 0
1657 LiveVirtRegs.setUniverse(NumVirtRegs); 0
1658 MayLiveAcrossBlocks.clear(); 0
1659 MayLiveAcrossBlocks.resize(NumVirtRegs); 0
1660 ----
1661 // Loop over all of the basic blocks, eliminating virtual register references ----
1662 for (MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) 0
1663 allocateBasicBlock(MBB); 0
1664 ----
1665 if (ClearVirtRegs) { 0
1666 // All machine operands and other references to virtual registers have been ----
1667 // replaced. Remove the virtual registers. ----
1668 MRI->clearVirtRegs(); 0
1669 } ----
1670 ----
1671 StackSlotForVirtReg.clear(); 0
1672 LiveDbgValueMap.clear(); 0
1673 return true; 0
1674 } ----
